---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const pageTitle = "Luigi";
---
<Layout pageTitle={pageTitle}>
    <div class="gif">
        <img width="300" height="259" alt="Space Doguri" src="/SpaceDoguri.webp"/>
    </div>

    <h4 style="color: red;">My portfolio is still under construction; some pages are not as polished as they should be, and some pages/features are not available yet. This message will disappear once I'm satisfied with its state. Please forgive a man lacking time üôè</h4>

    <h1>Luigi J.</h1>

    <small>Web Developer</small>
    <div class="socials">
        <a href="https://github.com/luigidotmoe"><img width="50" height="50" src="/GitHub.svg" alt="GitHub" title="GitHub"></a>
        <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/luigidotmoe"><img width="50" height="50" src="/LinkedIn.svg" alt="LinkedIn" title="LinkedIn"></a>    
    </div>

    <h2>About</h2>
    <p>
        I took my first steps into coding back in the late 2000s, fueled by a passion for creating new content for my favorite childhood 
        games (Metin2, Minecraft, Dofus). This passion led me to explore various development community forums, 
        and immersing myself in these online spaces ignited a curiosity about the underlying mechanisms that powered these forums. 
        Consequently, years later, I embarked on a journey to become a Web Developer.
    </p>
    <div class="button">
        <a href="/projects/">
            <button>My projects</button>
        </a>
    </div>

    <h2>Skills</h2>
    <div class="link-images">
        <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTML5"><img width="46" height="46" alt="HTML" title="HTML" src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/devicons/devicon/icons/html5/html5-plain.svg"/></a>
        <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CSS"><img width="46" height="46" alt="CSS" title="CSS" src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/devicons/devicon/icons/css3/css3-plain.svg"/></a>
        <a href="https://sass-lang.com/"><img width="46" height="46" alt="Sass" title="Sass" src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/devicons/devicon/icons/sass/sass-original.svg"/></a>
        <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JavaScript"><img width="46" height="46" alt="JavaScript" title="JavaScript" src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/devicons/devicon/icons/javascript/javascript-plain.svg"/></a>
        <a href="https://tailwindcss.com/"><img width="46" height="46" alt="TailwindCSS" title="TailwindCSS" src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/devicons/devicon/icons/tailwindcss/tailwindcss-plain.svg"/></a>
        <a href="https://getbootstrap.com/"><img width="46" height="46" alt="Bootstrap" title="Bootstrap" src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/devicons/devicon/icons/bootstrap/bootstrap-plain.svg"/></a>
        <a href="https://react.dev/"><img width="46" height="46" alt="React" title="React" src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/devicons/devicon/icons/react/react-original.svg"/></a>
        <a href="https://vuejs.org/"><img width="46" height="46" alt="VueJS" title="VueJS" src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/devicons/devicon/icons/vuejs/vuejs-original.svg"/></a>
        <a href="https://www.php.net/"><img width="46" height="46" alt="PHP" title="PHP" src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/devicons/devicon/icons/php/php-plain.svg"/></a>
        <a href="https://symfony.com/"><img width="46" height="46" alt="Symfony" title="Symfony" src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/devicons/devicon/icons/symfony/symfony-original.svg"/></a>
        <a href="https://www.mysql.com/"><img width="46" height="46" alt="MySQL" title="MySQL" src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/devicons/devicon/icons/mysql/mysql-original.svg"/></a>
        <a href="https://www.postgresql.org/"><img width="46" height="46" alt="PostgreSQL" title="PostgreSQL" src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/devicons/devicon/icons/postgresql/postgresql-original.svg"/></a>
    </div>

    <h2>Interests</h2>
    <p>
        Consuming way too much media of all kinds: Manga, Comics, Video Games, Books, Movies, Shows...
    </p>
    <p>
        I'm currently preparing the development of a project to backlog all this media consumption into a centralized app, 
        replacing my current stack of trackers that are often specialized in one media type.
    </p>
    <p>
        It wouldn't be me if I didn't mention that I'm a huge animal lover. 
        (I love my baby <a href="https://shanks.luigi.moe/" target="_blank">Shanks</a>)
    </p>
</Layout>

<style>
    /* h1 */
    h1 {
        margin-bottom: 1%;
    }

    /* small */
    small {
        background-color: #584966;
        color: #fdebf3;
        border-radius: 6px;
        font-family: 'Josefin Sans', sans-serif;
        font-weight: 600;
        padding: 0.3em 0.6em 0.2em;
        margin bottom:;
    }

    /* socials div */
    .socials {
        margin-top: 1%;
    }
    /* Button */
    button {
        background: rgba(0,0,0,0);
        border: 2px solid #584966;
        border-radius: 8px;
        color: #1e1e2e;
        font: 600 16px 'Josefin Sans', sans-serif;
        padding: 8px 16px;
        transition: background-color 0.4s, color 0.4s;
    }
    
    button:hover {
        background-color: #584966;
        color: #fdebf3  ;
        cursor: pointer;
    }

    .button {
        text-align: center;
    }

    /* Skill images */
    .link-images img {
        margin: 16px 4px;
    }

    @media only screen and (max-width: 600px) {
        .link-images img {
            height: 30px;
            width: 30px;
            margin: 16px 1px;
        }
    }
</style>
